article.headline: Portland St. 79, N. Illinois 58
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska -- Andre Murray and Phil Nelson scored 16 points each, Kyle Coston added 14 and Portland State scored the first 11 points of the second half to pull away for a 79-58 win over Northern Illinois in the first round of the Carrs/Safeway Great Alaska Shootout on Wednesday night. The Vikings, favored to win the Big Sky Conference, scored the final four points of the first half and surged to a comfortable lead behind an 13-2 run to begin the second half. Nelson started the spurt with a 3-pointer, and his thunderous one-handed dunk pushed the lead to 46-32. Northern Illinois was scoreless until Mike DiNunno's free throws with 16:29 left. Portland State (4-0) will face Hampton in the tournament semifinals on Friday. NIU (2-3) was led by Darion Anderson's 16 points. NIU plays host Alaska-Anchorage on Friday.
